Support=20
and report a code problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 721"><HR>
</A>
   <B>721</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> The controller attempted to write an error dump =
file to=20
the 5494 System Diskette because of a failure in the operational =
microcode.=20
However, the 5494 System Diskette was damaged or missing. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Write down the SRC displayed on the =
operator=20
panel. Insert a 5494 System Diskette into the controller and press =
<B>Enter</B>=20
to attempt to write the error dump file again. Contact 5494 support and =
report=20
the SRC. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The 5494 reinitializes after the error dump file is written. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>Pressing <B>Esc</B> bypasses the writing of the error dump file, =
and the=20
controller immediately reinitializes if a 5494 System Diskette is in the =

controller. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 722"><HR>
</A>
   <B>722</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> The controller attempted to write an error dump =
file to=20
the 5494 System Diskette because of a failure in the operational =
microcode.=20
However, the 5494 System Diskette was write-protected. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> The 5494 reinitializes automatically after =
approximately two=20
minutes if no action is taken. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Write down the SRC displayed on the =
operator=20
panel. Close the write-protect tab on the 5494 System Diskette. Press=20
<B>Enter</B> to attempt to write to the error dump file again. Contact =
5494=20
support and report the SRC. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The 5494 reinitializes after the error dump file is written. =
Pressing=20
<B>Esc</B> bypasses the writing of the error dump file, and the =
controller=20
immediately reinitializes. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 730"><HR>
</A>
   <B>730</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> A failure in the operational code has been =
detected. The=20
5494 has reinitialized itself and resumed operations. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Write down the SRC including the =
asterisks (**).=20
Then contact 5494 Support and report a code problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 999"><HR>
</A>
   <B>999</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> An incorrect request code has been entered by =
the user. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Press <B>Esc</B> to clear. To try the =
operation=20
again, press <B>Req</B>, type a valid request code, and press =
<B>Enter</B>. See=20
<A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDROPCMD">"Concurrent</A>=20
<A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDROPCMD">Mode=20
from the Operator Panel (Online)" in topic 6.2</A> for a list of the =
valid=20
request codes.=20
<HR>
<A name=3DMSG><A name=3DHDRSRC>
<H2>3.2 SRCs</H2></A></A><PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<BR>
</P></PRE>The following SRCs can appear on the left-hand side or =
right-hand side=20
of a workstation screen. Many of them can also appear on the right-hand =
side of=20
the 5494 LCD, accompanied by a message code on the left. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>SRCs are displayed on the right-hand side of the LCD and indicate =
the=20
failure of a FRU or an action required to resolve a problem. SRCs can =
range from=20
3 to 6 digits and can be generated by a POST, extended diagnostics, or =
the=20
operational code. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE><A name=3D"MSG 0000">
<HR>
</A><B>0000</B> <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Cause:</B> Help key not allowed. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed Help. However, either no SRC was displayed or the =
application=20
program does not support Help. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Continue entering information or refer to the meaning for =
the=20
previously displayed SRC and do the recovery procedure. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0001"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0001</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Keyboard overrun. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>A keyboard overrun occurred because the 5494 could not keep up =
with the=20
rate at which you were entering information. The last character entered =
was not=20
recognized. If type ahead has been enabled, your buffer is full. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue entering information. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0002"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0002</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Incorrect scan code. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The 5494 received an incorrect scan code from the workstation's =
keyboard.=20
Either the scan code is incorrect for the keyboard at the workstation, =
or an=20
error occurred in translating the keystroke. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and try to continue entering the data. If the error occurs =
again,=20
check the language code entered in the configuration for the =
workstation's=20
keyboard. If the keyboard language code entered in the configuration is =
correct,=20
contact the workstation service representative and report the problem. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0003"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0003</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Command or PF key is not valid. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed a Command key sequence, a PF key that is not supported =
or not=20
valid for the current field, or the Alt key sequence is not valid. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue, using the correct keys. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0004"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0004</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Data not allowed in this field. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You tried to enter data from the keyboard into a field where only =
an entry=20
from a magnetic stripe reader or a light pen is allowed. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Move the cursor to a field where data from the keyboard =
can be=20
entered. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0005"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0005</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Cursor in protected area of display. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You have tried to enter data; however, the cursor is not in an =
input field=20
on the display. Data cannot be entered in a protected area of the =
display. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and move the cursor to a valid input field. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0006"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0006</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Key following Sys Req Key not valid. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed a key that is not valid after the Sys Req Key and =
before the=20
Enter/Rec Adv or Error Reset. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and use a valid key sequence. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0007"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0007</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Mandatory entry field; you must enter data. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>There is at least one field on the screen into which you must =
enter data=20
before the screen can be changed or processed. (The cursor goes to the =
first=20
character position of the first mandatory entry field.) <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and enter the required data. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0008"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0008</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> This field must have alphabetic characters. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You tried to enter nonalphabetic characters into a mandatory =
alphabetic=20
field. Valid characters are A through Z, space, comma (,), period (.), =
hyphen=20
(-), apostrophe ('), and Dup. Dup can be used to duplicate these =
characters in=20
the field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue, using valid characters. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0009"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0009</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> This field must have numeric characters. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You tried to enter nonnumeric characters into a numeric-only =
field. Valid=20
characters are 0 through 9, space, comma (,), period (.), plus (+), =
minus (-),=20
and Dup. Dup can be used to duplicate these characters in the field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue, using valid characters. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0010"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0010</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Only characters 0-9 are allowed. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The key pressed is not valid for a signed numeric field. Valid =
entries are=20
0 through 9 and the Dup key. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue, using valid characters. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0011"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0011</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> You tried to enter data into the last position =
of a=20
signed numeric field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Make sure that the data is correct, and then exit the =
field by=20
using the Field -, Field +, or Field Exit key. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0012"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0012</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Insert mode; no room to insert data. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>There is no room to insert the data in this field. Either there is =
no more=20
room in the field or the cursor is in the last position of the field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>Do not use insert mode to change data or to enter the last =
character in=20
this field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Correct the field, if necessary, and continue. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0013"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0013</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Insert mode; only data keys permitted. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You tried to exit a field while the workstation was still in =
insert mode. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and exit the field normally. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0014"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0014</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Must fill field to exit. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed a function key that would move the cursor out of this =
field.=20
However, the requirements of this mandatory-fill field were not met. A=20
mandatory-fill field must be completely filled or left blank. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Enter data to fill the entire field, or move the cursor to =
the=20
start of the field and use Field -, Field +, or Field Exit to erase the =
contents=20
of the field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0015"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0015</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Modulo 10 or 11 check digit error. You entered =
data into=20
a self-check field, and the number you entered and the check digit do =
not=20
compare. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Make sure that you have entered the number and check digit =

correctly. If you entered them correctly, make sure that the number is =
valid for=20
a self-check field. If the numbers you are using are valid but this =
error still=20
occurs, contact the workstation service representative and report the =
problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0016"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0016</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Field - not valid in this field. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed Field - when the cursor was not in a numeric-only,=20
digits-only, or signed numeric field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Continue to enter data or press <B>Field</B> <B>Exit</B> =
to exit=20
the field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0017"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0017</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Mandatory-fill field; key pressed is not valid. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed the Field -, Field +, or Field Exit key. However, the=20
requirements for this mandatory-fill field were not met. A =
mandatory-fill field=20
must be completely filled unless you exit it from the first position of =
the=20
field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Enter data to the end of the field or move the cursor to =
the start=20
of the field and use Field -, Field +, or Field Exit to erase the =
contents of=20
the field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0018"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0018</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Key used to exit this field not valid. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The cursor is in a right-adjust or field-exit-required field, and =
you=20
pressed a data key. Use Field Exit to exit this field. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Press <B>Field</B> <B>Exit</B> to exit this field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0019"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0019</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Dup or Field Mark not permitted in this field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed Dup or Field Mark. However, the key is not permitted =
in this=20
field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Continue without using Dup or Field Mark in this field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0020"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0020</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Function key not valid for right-adjust field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed a function key that is not permitted in this field. =
Press=20
Field -, Field +, or Field Exit to exit this field before pressing one =
of the=20
following function keys: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<UL>
  <LI>Test Req=20
  <LI>Clear=20
  <LI>Enter/Rec Adv=20
  <LI>Print=20
  <LI>Help=20
  <LI>Roll=20
  <LI>Home (when the cursor is in the home position)=20
  <LI>PF/Cmd1-24=20
  <LI>Sys Req=20
  <LI>Rec Backspace. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, =
press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. The cursor is in the same position that it was when you =
pressed=20
the Function key. Continue by pressing Field -, Field +, or Field Exit. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0021"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0021</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Must enter data in mandatory entry field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The cursor is positioned in a mandatory entry field. You must =
enter data=20
into a mandatory entry field before you can exit the field by pressing =
the Field=20
-, Field +, or Field Exit key. You can exit from any position if no data =
is=20
entered. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and enter the required data. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0022"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0022</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> An AS/400 system error occurred. The status of =
the=20
current field is not known. This error can occur during an insert or =
delete=20
operation. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Check the display screen to determine if the insert or =
delete=20
function was completed correctly. If it was not, complete it correctly. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0023"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0023</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Hexadecimal mode; entry not valid. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The workstation is in hexadecimal mode but the first key pressed =
was not a=20
character 4 through 9 or A through F, or the second key pressed was not =
a=20
character 0 through 9 or A through F. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>This error also occurs when a hexadecimal code is used in a =
numeric-only,=20
signed-numeric, digits-only, alpha-only, or I/O field. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Continue by pressing the correct keys. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0024"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0024</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Decimal field; entry not valid. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed a key that is not valid. Only characters 0 through 9 =
and Dup=20
(if specified in the field format word) are allowed in this field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue by entering digits in this field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0026"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0026</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Field - entry not allowed. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed Field - to exit a numeric-only field, but the last =
position of=20
the field was not a character 0 through 9. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Correct the last position of this field or exit the field =
by using=20
a key other than Field - (for example, Field + or Field Exit). =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0027"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0027</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Cannot use undefined key. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed a key that is either blank or not defined for your=20
workstation. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue, using valid keys. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0029"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0029</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Diacritic character not valid. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The second key pressed during a diacritic key function did not =
produce a=20
valid diacritic character. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and enter a valid combination. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0031"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0031</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Data buffer overflow. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The data received from the magnetic stripe reader (MSR) card was =
longer=20
than the maximum allowed. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and use another MSR card. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0032"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0032</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> MSR error. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>The data from the Magnetic Stripe Reader (MSR) card was not =
received=20
correctly. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and pass the card through the MSR again. If the error is =
still=20
present after several attempts, contact the MSR service representative =
and=20
report the problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0033"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0033</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> MSR data not authorized. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The data received from the Magnetic Stripe Reader (MSR) card was =
secured=20
data (for example, an operator ID card), and this field was not =
specified for=20
secured data. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B> and continue using a correct MSR card. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0034"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0034</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> MSR data exceeds length of field. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The data received from the Magnetic Stripe Reader (MSR) card will =
not fit=20
into the active input field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Pass another card through the MSR. If the error is still =
present,=20
contact the AS/400 system operator and report a possible programming =
error. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0035"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0035</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> MSR error. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>The card to be read was incorrectly inserted into the Magnetic =
Stripe=20
Reader (MSR), was incorrectly made, or is damaged. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Put the card to be read through the MSR again. If the =
error is=20
still present after several attempts, try another MSR or test the MSR =
card to=20
make sure that the problem is not caused by a defective card. If the =
error is=20
still present, contact the MSR service representative and report the =
problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0036"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0036</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Cursor select not allowed in field-exit-required =
state. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>You pressed Cursor Select while in field-exit-required state. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Complete the current field or use Field Exit or Field =
Backspace to=20
position the cursor. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 0037"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0037</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> You pressed Cursor Select in a nonselectable =
field. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> At the workstation, press <B>Error</B>=20
<B>Reset</B>. Then, position the cursor on a field where the cursor =
select=20
function is valid. For more information, refer to your workstation =
operator's=20

    <LI>Communication line is attached to the modem. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>If you find no problems, continue with the =
next step. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B>For</B> <B>a</B> <B>new</B> <B>or</B> <B>changed</B>=20

5494=20
  configuration and the equipment match. (See <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

  <A=20
  =

02/4.4?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRVJC">the=20
  5494 Configuration" in topic 4.4</A>.) If the communication mode is=20
  synchronous data link control (SDLC), pay particular attention to the =
setting=20
  for the communications line type. Valid selections are: =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>Leased line=20
    <LI>Switched line=20
    <LI>Switched line/V.25 bis. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>If the communications line type is correct, =
continue with step <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.2?DT=3D19961016091447#LISSS22">3</A>.=20
  If not, correct the setting and try the job again. (To correct the =
setting,=20
  refer to the <CITE>IBM</CITE> <CITE>5494</CITE> <CITE>Remote</CITE>=20
  <CITE>Control</CITE> <CITE>Unit</CITE> <CITE>User's</CITE> =
<CITE>Guide</CITE>=20
  for instructions.) <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3DLISss22></PRE>
  <LI><B>For</B> <B>an</B> <B>existing,</B> <B>unchanged</B> =
<B>installation</B>=20
  <B>or</B> <B>configuration:</B> Verify</A> that the problem is not in =
the 5494=20
  or the 5494 communication interface cable. Turn the 5494 power =
<B>OFF</B>=20
  (<B>0</B>) and then back <B>ON</B> (<B>|</B>) to run POST. During =
POST, the=20
  5494 runs automatic cable wrap to the end of the 5494 communication =
cable to=20
  verify that the 5494 circuitry and cable are good. Wait for about 30 =
seconds=20
  after the Ready LED is lit. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>If a different SRC is displayed, follow the CE action for that =
SRC. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <LI>If the same SRC is displayed, automatic cable wrap has =
determined that=20
    the problem is in the modem or the network. Ask the customer to =
contact one=20
    of the following: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <UL>
      <LI>The network service representative and report that the network =
is out=20
      of service, or that no signal is being received from the modem or =
DCE. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
      <LI>The modem service representative and report that the DSR line =
from the=20
      modem is inactive when it should be active. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
    <LI>If no SRC is displayed, the problem could be due to a temporary=20
    condition. Retry the job. If the problem reoccurs, ask the customer =
to=20
    report it to the modem/DCE or network representative. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

</A><B>0049</B>=20

<A name=3D"MSG 0050"><HR>
</A>
   <B>0050</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Error in ready for sending (RFS) signal, also =
known as=20
the clear to send (CTS) signal, received from the modem or data=20
circuit-terminating equipment (DCE). This error is posted when one of =
the=20
following has occurred: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<UL>
  <LI>The RFS line is inactive for up to 30 seconds while the ready to =
send=20
  (RTS) line is active. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>The RFS line is active when the RTS line is inactive (except =
during V.25=20
  bis call establishment). <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<OL type=3D1>
  <LI>Verify that the: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>5494 cable to the modem or DCE is securely connected=20
    <LI>Modem or DCE is turned <B>ON</B>=20
    <LI>Communication line is attached to the modem. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
  <LI>If no problem is found, and the 5494 is attached to an X.25 =
network, go to=20
  step <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.2?DT=3D19961016091447#LISCH3E502">4</A>.=20
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B>For</B> <B>a</B> <B>new</B> <B>or</B> <B>changed</B>=20
  <B>configuration</B> <B>or</B> <B>installation:</B> <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <OL type=3Da>
    <LI>Make sure that the following 5494 configuration settings are =
correct for=20
    the system and match the configuration for the modem. (See <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.4?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRVJC">"Verifying=20
    the 5494 Configuration" in</A> <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.4?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRVJC">topic=20
    4.4</A>.) <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <UL>
      <LI>Half-duplex or duplex=20
      <LI>Multipoint or point-to-point. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
    <LI>If the settings are correct, continue with step <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.2?DT=3D19961016091447#LISCH3E502">4</A>.=20
    If not, correct the settings and try the job again. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></OL><A name=3DLISch3e502><PRE></PRE>
  <LI><B>For</B> <B>an</B> <B>existing,</B> <B>unchanged</B> =
<B>installation</B>=20
  <B>or</B> <B>configuration:</B></A> Verify that the problem is not in =
the 5494=20
  or the 5494 communication interface cable. Turn the 5494 power =
<B>OFF</B>=20
  (<B>0</B>) and then back <B>ON</B> (<B>|</B>) to run POST. During =
POST, the=20
  5494 runs automatic cable wrap to the end of the 5494 communication =
cable to=20
  verify that the 5494 circuitry and cable are good. Wait for about 30 =
seconds=20
  after the Ready LED is lit. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>If a different SRC is displayed, follow the CE action for that =
SRC. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <LI>If the same SRC is displayed, automatic cable wrap determined =
that the=20
    problem is in the DCE or modem. Ask the customer to contact the =
modem or DCE=20
    service representative and report that the RFS signal received from =
the=20
    modem or DCE is not responding correctly to the RTS signal sent from =
the=20
    5494. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <LI>If no SRC is displayed, the problem could be due to a temporary=20
    condition. Retry the job. If the problem reoccurs, ask the customer =
to=20
    report it to the modem/DCE or network representative. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>

<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> For an =
ideographic error, at the=20

enter the=20
correct information in the field. For a bidirectional error, ask the =
customer to=20
press <B>Error</B> <B>Reset</B> at the workstation. <PRE></PRE><PRE =

<BR>| time. It has one of the following causes: <PRE></PRE><PRE =

</PRE>
<OL type=3D1>
  <LI>| If the customer is on configuration screen 2 and has configured =
<BR>| to=20
  use concurrent host attachment, and the cursor is within an <BR>| Hx:1 =
field: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>| The Hx:1 and Hx:2 fields are joined together to form the <BR>| =
fully=20
    qualified name of the AS/400 system. When configured <BR>| for =
concurrent=20
    host attachment, the fully qualified name <BR>| must be unique for =
each=20
    host. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>

<BR>|=20
  within a DLCI field: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>| The DLCI in the field pointed to with the cursor is the same =
<BR>| as=20
    another frame relay-token-ring bridge DLCI or as a Host <BR>| DLCI =
on screen=20
    2. All DLCIs must be unique. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
  <LI>| If the customer is on configuration screen 3 and the cursor is =
<BR>| in=20
  the frame relay ring number field: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>| Each ring number within a network must be unique. <BR>| =
Therefore, the=20
    frame relay ring number cannot be the same as <BR>| the LAN ring =
number. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
  <LI>| If the customer is on configuration screen 3 and the cursor is =
<BR>| in=20
  the frame relay MAC address field: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>| The frame relay MAC address must be different than the 5494 =
<BR>|=20
    token-ring LAN address on screen 1. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
<P>
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL></LI></OL><PRE></PRE><BR>| <B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> =
Check the configuration. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<UL>

<BR>| for=20
  the AS/400 system is unique for each configured host. If <BR>| you =
want to=20
  configure the 5494 to communicate with the same <BR>| AS/400 system =
using=20
  different host names, for example H1 and H2, <BR>| you must create an =
alias=20
  for the AS/400 system: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>

alias. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>

<BR>|=20
    alias as the AS/400 LU name for the other Hx configuration. =

<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>

<BR>| your=20
  5494 SNA traffic and your 5494 bridge traffic even if it is <BR>| =
flowing=20
  between the same two points. Assign a second DLCI. If <BR>| two FR-TR =
bridge=20
  DLCIs are the same, remove one of them. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>| For problem number 3: Each ring number within a network must be =
<BR>|=20
  unique. Therefore, the frame relay ring number cannot be the <BR>| =
same as the=20
  LAN ring number. Change one of the ring numbers. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->

<BR>|=20

must be=20
  different from the 5494 Token-ring address. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->

</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE><BR>| Correct the configuration. =

damaged one. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

office.=20

</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Hardware failure. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> This is the result of a timing problem =
between=20
the planar and an adapter installed in the 5494. Replace and verify the =
adapters=20
one at a time. If this does not solve the problem, replace the planar. =
Be sure=20
to reinstall the adapters that have been verified as operating =
correctly. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

problem but=20

at a=20

href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

adapters=20
that have been verified as operating correctly. <PRE></PRE><PRE =

   <B>120</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><BR>| <B>Cause:</B> Hardware initialization required. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> The information stored in the 5494 about =
the=20
installed adapters and features does not match that determined by the =
POST. This=20
condition can result when adapters or features have just been installed, =

removed, or changed, or if there has been a failure in <BR>| the 5494. =
Press the=20
<B>Enter</B> key on the 5494 keypad and follow the <BR>| message codes =
to run=20
setup. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

</A>
   <B>152(s,p)</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Cable failure. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Isolate the problem as follows: =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<OL type=3D1>
  <LI>Turn the 5494 power <B>OFF</B> (<B>0</B>). Remove the cable =
connected to=20
  port <B>p</B> (see <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.2?DT=3D19961016091447#TBLPORT">Table=20
  8</A>). Then, turn the 5494 power back <B>ON</B> (<B>|</B>). If this =
error=20
  code does not reappear, repair or replace the cable.=20
  <LI>If the problem continues, replace the host-twinaxial adapter in =
slot=20
  <B>s</B>. See <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/5.7.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRREC">"Twinaxial=20
  Adapter and Twinaxial Expansion Adapter</A> <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/5.7.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRREC">Removal=20
  and Replacement" in topic 5.7.2</A>. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
</PRE><BR>| <B>Note:</B> The customer may choose to operate the 5494 =
with=20
  these <BR>| cabling problems until these cabling problems are =
repaired. To=20
  <BR>| do so, press the <B>Enter</B> key on the 5494 keypad. Message=20
  <TT>002-05|</TT> <BR>| <TT>.......</TT> <TT>0</TT> appears. Type =
<B>1</B> to=20
  select IPL in normal mode and <BR>| press <B>Enter</B>. The 5494 =
attempts to=20
  use all the twinaxial ports <BR>| and will log any resulting errors. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

are=20
operating correctly. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 166(s,c)"><HR>
</A>
   <B>166(s,c)</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> Hardware failure. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Replace the host-twinaxial adapter in =
slot=20
<B>s</B>. If this does not solve the problem, replace the communication =
cable=20
(<B>c</B> indicates the cable type). <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>
<DL>
  <DT>If <B>c</B>=3D
  <DD><B>1</B> X.21=20
  <DT>
  <DD><B>2</B> V.35=20
  <DT>
  <DD><B>3</B> EIA 232D <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></DD></DL>If the problem persists, replace the power supply (see =
<A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/5.7.9?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRRPS">"Power=20
Supply</A> <A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/5.7.9?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRRPS">Removal=20
and Replacement" in topic 5.7.9</A>), and then, if necessary, the planar =
(see <A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/5.7.10?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRRPC">"Planar=20
Removal and Replacement" in topic 5.7.10</A>). Be sure to reinstall the=20
communication cable.=20

procedures for=20
ending a communication link in the <CITE>IBM</CITE> <CITE>5494</CITE>=20
<CITE>Remote</CITE> <CITE>Control</CITE> <CITE>Unit</CITE> =

   <B>100200</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> (X.25) An ANSWER command was entered for a =
permanent=20
virtual circuit (PVC). <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

command. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>If the customer is trying to initiate communications on a switched =
virtual=20
circuit (SVC), the 5494 configuration is incorrect. (The virtual circuit =
type=20
for this 5494 is defined as PVC only.) Ask the customer to verify the =
5494=20
configuration, paying particular attention to the setting for Virtual =
Circuit=20
Type. The possible selections are: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>
<UL>
  <LI>PVC only=20
  <LI>SVC answer only=20
  <LI>Other (multiple PVC, multiple SVC, or SVC call). <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>Ask the customer to try to restart =
communication with the AS/400=20
system. If still unsuccessful, ask the customer to call the AS/400 =
system=20
operator. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>If the subscription is for modulo 128 and the customer received =
this=20
  error, the 5494 has been configured for modulo 8 instead of modulo =
128. Ask=20
  the customer to change the value of Packet Level Sequence Numbering =
from=20
  modulo 8 to modulo 128 in the 5494 configuration. (Refer to the AS/400 =

  Connection Worksheet-X.25 to verify this value.) <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL>Ask the customer to try again with the correct =
entry.=20

because it is greater than 15 and modulo 128 is specified. =

the X.25=20
DTE port for the number called is actually busy. If it is not busy, make =
sure=20
that the number configured in the 5494 for the called system is correct. =
If the=20
error persists, ask the customer to contact the network service =
representative. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Wait. Then, ask the customer to try the =
operation=20
again. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> The network might impose restrictions on how fast the =

operation can be retried. To alleviate network congestion, ask the =
customer to=20
consult the network service representative. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>If the error reoccurs, ask the customer to report it, including =
the=20
diagnostic code (<VAR>dd</VAR>), to the network service representative =
and the=20
ALS operator. See <A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> An XID3 command specified a maximum basic =
transmission=20
unit (BTU) length less than 265 bytes. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
</PRE>There is a system problem or configuration problem in the ALS. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> This is an AS/400 system problem. Ask the =

customer to contact the ALS operator or network service representative =
and=20
report the problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

   <B>410800</B>

</A>
   <B>411200</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> The ALS reported an error in the Exchange =
Station=20
Identification (XID) response received from the 5494. There could be a =
mismatch=20
between the 5494 and the ALS configuration. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The 3-byte error offset received in the control vector is logged =
as sense=20
data. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<OL type=3D1>
  <LI>While this SRC is being displayed on the 5494 operator panel, =
press the=20
  <B>right</B> <B>arrow</B> (&gt;) on the keypad to display the sense =
bytes for=20
  this SRC. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>Record this SRC and the sense bytes. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>For a new or changed installation or configuration: =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>Verify the 5494 configuration. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>Check the 5494 ID number. If one was configured, verify that it =
is=20
    correct. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <LI>Check the 5494 CP name. Verify that it is correct and that it is =
the=20
    same value the ALS expects. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>If you find no problem, go to step <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.2?DT=3D19961016091447#LISSSS">4</A>.=20
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3DLISsss></PRE>
  <LI>For an existing, unchanged installation or configuration:</A> =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>If the configuration is correct, ask the customer to call the ALS=20
  operator and make sure that the controller descriptions for the 5494 =
are=20
  active. If they are active and the problem persists, ask the customer =
to=20
  report this SRC and the sense bytes to the ALS operator or the network =
service=20
  representative. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></OL><A name=3D"MSG 420000">
<HR>
</A><B>420000</B>=20
<P><PRE></PRE><B>Cause:</B> A timeout occurred on completion of a Change =
Number of=20
Sessions (CNOS) exchange. This could be caused by an AS/400 system or=20
communication network problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The first sense byte identifies which AS/400 system the 5494 was=20
attempting to contact when the error occurred. The meanings are: 00 =3D =
H1, 40 =3D=20
H2, 80 =3D H3, and C0 =3D H4. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Try to restart communication with the =
AS/400=20
system. If still unsuccessful, ask the customer to report the problem to =
the=20
AS/400 system operator. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

contains=20

the=20

href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

Screen" in</A> <A=20

7.8 </A>for instructions on displaying the LSID. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Turn the power <B>OFF</B> and back =
<B>ON</B> at=20
the PWS, and then restart the PWS communication program. If necessary, =
make sure=20
the PWS communication program is correctly installed and configured. =

<A name=3D"MSG 4525xx"><HR>
</A>
   <B>4525xx</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> The LAN link with the PWS terminated due to =
receipt of a=20
frame with an Origin-Destination Assignor Identifier (ODAI) value that =
is not=20
valid in the transmission header. All sessions for this PWS are =
terminated. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Turn the power <B>OFF</B> and back =
<B>ON</B> at=20
the PWS, and then restart the PWS communication program. If necessary, =
make sure=20
the PWS communication program is correctly installed and configured. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 460000"><HR>
</A>
   <B>460000</B>

session=20
address. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> This SRC could occur as part of normal =
session=20
termination. If this error occurs frequently, and disrupts active =
customer=20
sessions, ask the customer to report the error to the AS/400 system =
operator. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

</PRE><B>For</B> <B>a</B> <B>new</B> <B>or</B> <B>changed</B>=20

been=20
configured. Refer to the <CITE>IBM</CITE> <CITE>5494</CITE> =
<CITE>Remote</CITE>=20
<CITE>Control</CITE> <CITE>Unit</CITE> <CITE>User's</CITE> =
<CITE>Guide</CITE>=20
and work with the customer to configure the 5494. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>For</B> <B>an</B> <B>existing,</B> <B>unchanged</B> =
<B>installation</B>=20
<B>or</B> <B>configuration:</B> There could be a problem with the 5494 =
storage.=20
When the 5494 attempted to use the backup copy of the configuration on =
the=20
system diskette, it could not find one. The 5494 POST may have already=20
identified the problem and you could have decided to use the 5494 with =
the=20
storage problem anyway. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<UL>
  <LI>If a storage problem has already been identified and you want to =
use the=20
  5494 anyway, the 5494 must either be reconfigured or a 5494 System =
Diskette=20
  that has a backup copy of the configuration file must be used. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>If a storage problem has not been identified, you should run =
extended=20
  diagnostics to further isolate the problem. See <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

  <DD>EC level is not valid.=20
  <DT>02
  <DD>EC level length is not valid.=20
  <DT>03
  <DD>EC data level is not valid.=20
  <DT>05
  <DD>Change file length is not valid.=20
  <DT>10
  <DD>Change section length is not valid.=20
  <DT>20

installed from=20
  the system diskette. No AS/400 system changes have been installed. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></DD></DL><PRE></PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Try the power-on =
sequence again. If the=20
problem reoccurs, insert the backup diskette. Turn the 5494 power =
<B>OFF</B>=20
(<B>0</B>), and then back <B>ON</B> (<B>|</B>). <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->

report a possible 5494 code problem. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =

  in topic 4.4</A>). It may be too low. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =

  retry count. Refer to the <CITE>IBM</CITE> <CITE>5494</CITE>=20

href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

(Offline)" in topic 4.2</A>. If extended diagnostics do not detect a =

call 5494 Support and report the SRC and sense data. <PRE></PRE><PRE =

<A name=3D"MSG 540404"><HR>

   <B>540404</B>

address=20

<CITE>Control</CITE>=20
  <CITE>Unit</CITE> <CITE>User's</CITE> <CITE>Guide</CITE>), making sure =
that=20

  <CITE>Control</CITE> <CITE>Unit</CITE> <CITE>User's</CITE> =

</A><B>540407</B>=20
<P><PRE></PRE><B>Cause:</B> (LAN AS/400 Attachment) The 5494 detected an =

</PRE>Sense data consisting of a 1-byte cause code and the 6-byte AS/400 =
LAN=20
address is available by pressing the <B>right</B> <B>arrow</B> (&gt;) on =
the=20
5494 keypad when this error is displayed. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>The cause code is one of the following: <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<DL>
  <DT>22=20
  <DD>Error on frame transmission=20
  <DT>23=20
  <DD>Error in frame transmitted or read-back checking=20
  <DT>24=20
  <DD>Unauthorized MAC frame. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

or=20
  Ethernet configuration retry count (see <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

  <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=

  5494 Configuration" in topic 4.4</A>). It may be too low. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>Work with the customer to reconfigure the 5494 to increase the =
retry=20
  count. Refer to the <CITE>IBM</CITE> <CITE>5494</CITE> =
<CITE>Remote</CITE>=20
  <CITE>Control</CITE> <CITE>Unit</CITE> <CITE>User's</CITE> =
<CITE>Guide</CITE>=20
  for instructions. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI>Try the transmission again. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRUNNING">Extended=20
Diagnostics (Offline)" in topic 4.2</A>. If extended diagnostics do not =
detect a=20
problem, call 5494 Support and report the SRC and sense data. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 560407"><HR>
</A>
   <B>560407</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> (Frame Relay) The 5494 detected an error when it =

transmitted a frame. The data link is disconnected. The 5494 continues =
to send=20
TEST commands to the ALS to reestablish the connection. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>Sense data consisting of a 1-byte cause code and a 6-byte =
hexadecimal=20
frame-relay address is available. The cause code is one of the =
following: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<DL>
  <DT>22=20
  <DD>Error in frame transmission=20
  <DT>23=20
  <DD>Error in frame transmitted or read-back checking=20
  <DT>24=20
  <DD>Unauthorized medium access control (MAC) frame. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></DD></DL><PRE></PRE>The last three digits of the frame-relay =
address is the data link=20
connection identifier (DLCI). <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> To obtain sense data, press the right arrow key on =
the 5494=20
keypad when this SRC is displayed. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> The 5494 host-twinaxial adapter may be =
defective.=20
Run extended diagnostics and test all 5494 hardware. See <A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRUNNING">"Running</A>=20
<A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRRUNNING">Extended=20
Diagnostics (Offline)" in topic 4.2</A>. If extended diagnostics do not =
detect a=20
problem, call 5494 Support and report the SRC and sense data. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG 560408"><HR>
</A>
   <B>560408</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> (Frame Relay) A command to the 5494 =
host-twinaxial=20
adapter has failed. The sense bytes are <VAR>xxyy</VAR>, where =
<VAR>xx</VAR>=20
represents the command that was issued to the adapter and <VAR>yy</VAR>=20
represents the return code from the adapter. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> To obtain sense data, press the right arrow key on =
the 5494=20
keypad when this SRC is displayed. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =

<A name=3D"MSG 560409"><HR>
</A>
   <B>560409</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> (Frame Relay) A configured data link connection=20
identifier (DLCI) has not been reported by the network. The 5494 =
attempts to=20
contact the network using all DLCIs configured for hosts H1 - H4. The =
sense=20
bytes xxxx identify which DLCI has not been reported. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> To obtain sense data, press the right arrow key on =
the 5494=20
keypad when this SRC is displayed. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> If the DLCI noted in the sense data is =
for a=20
configured host other than the current one you are attempting to =
contact, ignore=20
this message. The 5494 continues attempts to contact the network on this =
DLCI,=20
but you should obtain a sign-on screen through your current connection. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>If the DLCI noted is for the current AS/400 system you are =
attempting to=20
contact <BR>then: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<OL type=3D1>
  <LI><B>For</B> <B>a</B> <B>new</B> <B>or</B> <B>changed</B>=20
  <B>installation</B> <B>or</B> <B>configuration</B>: You may have =
entered the=20
  DLCI incorrectly in the configuration information. If the DLCI in the =
sense=20
  data is not the assigned one, reconfigure the 5494 and correct the =
DLCI=20
  parameter. If the DLCI is correct, continue with the next step. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B>For</B> <B>an</B> <B>existing</B> <B>or</B> <B>unchanged</B>=20
  <B>installation</B> <B>or</B> <B>configuration</B>: There may be a =
temporary=20
  problem in the network. Call your network provider and report the =
problem. The=20
  5494 continues attempts to connect to the network at 30 second =
intervals. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></OL><A name=3D"MSG 560410">
<HR>
</A><B>560410</B>=20
<P><PRE></PRE><B>Cause:</B> (Frame Relay) A configured data link =
connection=20
identifier (DLCI) has been reported as not active by the network. The =
5494=20
attempts to contact the network using all DLCIs configured for hosts H1 =
- H4.=20
The sense bytes xxxx identify which DLCI has been reported as not =
active. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> To obtain sense data, press the right arrow key on =
the 5494=20
keypad when this SRC is displayed. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> The DLCI may be inactive due to a =
temporary=20
problem in the network. If the DLCI noted in the sense data is for a =
configured=20
host other than the current one you are attempting to contact, ignore =
this=20
message. The 5494 continues attempts to connect to the network on this =
DLCI, but=20
you should obtain a sign-on screen through your connection. =

attempting to=20

DLCI. The=20
5494 continues attempts to connect to the network at 30 second =
intervals. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

-->
</PRE>
  <DT><B>xxxxxxxxxx</B>
  <DD>Addressing information for the location of the failure. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></DD></DL><PRE></PRE><B>CE</B> <B>Action:</B> Call 5494 =
Support and report a code failure=20
and this SRC. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<A name=3D"MSG **xxxxxxxxxx"><HR>
</A>
   <B>**xxxxxxxxxx</B>
<P>
</P></PRE><B>Cause:</B> 5494 code error detected during operation. The =
5494=20
reinitialized itself and resumed operations. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<DL>
  <DT><B>**</B>=20
  <DD>Software error caused reinitialization to occur <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <DT><B>xxxxxxxxxx</B>
  <DD>Addressing information for the location of the failure. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->

and this SRC.=20

<HR>
<A name=3DHDREDF>
<H2>4.1 5494 Extended Diagnostics Flow</H2></A><PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<P>
<BR>
</P></PRE>
<P>This topic contains the reference information you need to perform the =

procedures in Topic 2 and actions in Topic 3. Topics 2 and 3 refer you =
to a=20
specific task in this topic, when necessary. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- lblbox -->
    ___ <B>Attention!</B> =
_________________________________________________________=20
   |                                                                     =
   |
   | Make sure that <B>all</B> sessions are logged off before you =
perform any of   |
   | the following tasks:                                                =
   |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   | =B0   Run extended diagnostics.                                     =
     |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   | =B0   Turn the 5494 power <B>OFF</B> (<B>0</B>).                    =
                   |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   | =B0   Disconnect any cable from the 5494.                           =
     |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   |                                                                     =
   |
   =
|________________________________________________________________________=
|
<P>
</P></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
   Most of the procedures in this topic instruct you to use extended
   diagnostics to determine the 5494 problem.  While extended =
diagnostics are
   being run, the 5494 is not communicating with the AS/400 system.
<P>
</P></PRE>See <A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.1?DT=3D19961016091447#FIGFLOWCH">Figure=20
9</A>. The instructions for running extended diagnostics follow in =
topic<A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPTRXT">=20
4.2</A>. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- figure -->
<A name=3DFIGFLOWCH>   <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/picture-25?mode=3Dzoom"><IMG alt=3D"PICTURE 25" =
src=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/bookmgr/pictures/co2v4002.199610160=
91447.P25.gif"></A>          </A>
<P>
<P>
   Figure 9. Extended Diagnostics Flow Chart
</P></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
<HR>
<A name=3DHDRRUNNING>
<H2>4.2 Running Extended Diagnostics (Offline)</H2></A><PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
<BR>
<A name=3DSPTRXT></P></PRE>
<OL type=3D1>
  <LI><B></B>Turn the 5494 power <B>OFF</B> (<B>0</B>).</A> =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B></B>Remove the system diskette from the diskette drive. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B></B>Because extended diagnostics automatically perform a cable =
wrap=20
  test on the cables that connect the 5494 to the modem or DCE and to a =
LAN=20
  (Token-Ring or Ethernet network), it is important that these cables, =
if=20
  present, are connected correctly before beginning extended =
diagnostics. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <UL>
    <LI>For external communications cable (modem or DCE connection), the =
cable=20
    must be connected to the 5494 but does not need to be connected to =
the modem=20
    or DCE. The diagnostics will automatically perform the cable wrap =
test. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <LI>For Token-Ring connections using: <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
    <UL>
      <LI>IBM Cabling System data connectors, the cable must be =
connected to the=20
      5494 and disconnected from the LAN. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
      <LI>Any other type of cabling connectors, disconnect the cable =
from the=20
      Token-Ring adapter and connect the wrap plug, provided with the =
cable, to=20
      the Token-Ring adapter. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
    <LI>For Ethernet connections using: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- =
* -->
</PRE>
    <UL>
      <LI>10BASE2 or 10BASE5, the 5494 should be connected to the LAN or =
to a=20
      wrap plug. If this is not possible, answer "no" to the panel that =
asks if=20
      the 5494 is connected to the LAN. This will prevent the wrap test =
from=20
      being performed. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
      <LI>10BASE-T, no wrap test is performed and no LAN connection is=20
      necessary. If the 5494 is connected to the LAN, it may be left =
connected. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE><B>Note:</B> Make sure that the extended =
diagnostic test for the=20
    Ethernet adapter is started from the CE main menu. <PRE></PRE><PRE =
width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></UL><PRE></PRE>
  <LI><B></B>Turn the 5494 power <B>ON</B> (<B>|</B>). Wait =
approximately 1=20
  minute while the POST is running. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE>
  <LI><B></B>When the message code 003-02 is displayed on the LCD, to =
begin=20
  extended diagnostics: <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <OL type=3Da>
    <LI><B></B>Insert the system diskette.=20
    <LI><B></B>Pull the keypad out of the 5494.=20
    <LI><B></B>Type <B>0</B>.=20
    <LI><B></B>Press <B>Enter</B>. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * =
-->
</PRE></LI></OL><PRE></PRE><B>Note:</B> If any other message code is =
displayed on the LCD,=20
  look up the message code in<A=20
  =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.1?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRMESSAGE">=20
  "Message Codes" in topic 3.1</A> to determine the next action. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B></B>When the message code 020-01 is displayed, press and hold=20
  <B>Alt</B> and press <B>PF1</B> to access the CE main menu (030-01). =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><B>Note:</B> If the 5494 has an Ethernet adapter and you are =
running=20
  "Test All 5494 Hardware", run the test <B>only</B> from the CE Main =
Menu=20
  (030-01). When running from the Main Menu (020-01), false errors may =
occur=20
  that indicate the Ethernet adapter is defective when it is not. =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <LI><B></B>Find the function you wish to access in the following table =
and=20
  follow the appropriate steps. The functions described are: =
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE>
  <DL>
    <DT><B>1</B>=20
    <DD>View 5494 features, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT1">4.2</A>.=20

    <DT><B>2</B>=20
    <DD>Test all 5494 hardware, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT2">4.2</A>.=20

    <DT><B>3</B>=20
    <DD>Verify or set date and time, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT3">4.2</A>.=20

    <DT><B>4</B>=20
    <DD>Run setup to verify or set the Token-Ring speed, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT4">4.2</A>,=20
    or to verify or select Ethernet media type, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT4A">4.2</A>.=20

    <DT><B>5</B>=20
    <DD>Test selected 5494 hardware, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT5">4.2</A>.=20

    <DT><B>6</B>=20
    <DD>View the 5494 error log, in topic <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPT6">4.2</A>.=20
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE></DD></DL><PRE></PRE>
  <LI><B></B>Press <B>Esc</B> to exit the extended diagnostics and =
restart the=20
  5494. <PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
<P>
</P></PRE></LI></OL><PRE></PRE>See <A=20
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.1?DT=3D19961016091447#FIGFLOWCH">Figure=20
9 in topic 4.1</A> if you have questions about the flow of extended =
diagnostics.=20
<PRE></PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- * -->
</PRE><PRE width=3D132><!-- table -->
<A name=3DTBLTBLUNIQ119></A></PRE>
<TABLE border=3D1 cellpading=3D"3">
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TH style=3D"FONT-WEIGHT: normal" width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> =

    <TH style=3D"FONT-WEIGHT: normal" width=3D"75%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> =

</FONT></PRE></TH></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>View</B> <B>5494</B>       =

<A name=3DSPT1> <B>features</B>        </A>
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20

                =20

                =20
                 </FONT></PRE></TD>
    <TD width=3D"75%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>1.</B>  Press <B>Enter</B> =
to display the adapters and amount  =20
     of storage installed in the 5494.               =20
                                                     =20
 <B>2.</B>  The feature information is identified by message=20
     codes displayed on the left-hand side of the    =20
     LCD.  Use the <B>up</B> and <B>down</B> <B>arrows</B> to scroll     =
 =20
     through the feature information.                =20
                                                     =20
     See <A =

to determine   =20
     the meaning of the message codes displayed while=20
     viewing the 5494 features.                      =20
                                                     =20
     Press <B>Esc</B> to exit this information.              =
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>Test</B> <B>all</B> =
<B>5494</B>  =20
<A name=3DSPT2> <B>hardware</B>        </A>
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                 </FONT></PRE></TD>
    <TD width=3D"75%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>1.</B>  Type <B>2</B> and =
press <B>Enter</B>.                         =20
                                                     =20
 <B>2.</B>  Message codes such as 031-01, 032-01, and 033-01=20
     will be displayed as the tests are run.  Manual =20
     intervention (for example, removing the diskette=20
     from the diskette drive) will be required for   =20
     some tests.  A message code will be displayed to=20
     indicate the action that is required.           =20
                                                     =20
 <B>3.</B>  If no problem is found, message code 030-04 will=20
     be displayed.  Press <B>Esc</B> until message code     =20
     030-01 is displayed, and then see "View the 5494=20
     error log" in topic <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/4.2?DT=3D19961016091447#SPTVIEWEL">4.2</A>.                        =20
                                                     =20
     If any other message code is displayed, see     =20
     <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/3.1?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRMESSAGE">"Message Codes" in topic 3.1</A>. =
                   </FONT></PRE></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>Verify</B> <B>or</B> =
<B>set</B>  =20
<A name=3DSPT3> <B>date</B> <B>and</B> <B>time</B>   </A>
                =20
                =20

                 </FONT></PRE></TD>
    <TD width=3D"75%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> The following steps explain =
how to set the date and =20
 time using extended diagnostics.                    =20
                                                     =20
 You can also use concurrent mode to set the date and=20
 time.  See <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2.14?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRDATE">"Setting 5494 Date" in topic =
6.2.14</A> and  =20
 <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2.15?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRTIME">"Setting 5494 Time" in topic =
6.2.15</A> for             =20
 instructions.                                       =20
                                                     =20
 <B>1.</B>  Press <B>3</B> and <B>Enter</B> to access the set date and   =
 =20
     time function.                                  =20
                                                     =20
 <B>2.</B>  When the message code 023-01 is displayed,      =20
     change the current date.  To change the current =20
     date:                                           =20
                                                     =20
     =B0   Use the <B>left</B> and <B>right</B> <B>arrows</B> to move =
the   =20
         cursor.                                     =20
                                                     =20
     =B0   Use the numbers to enter the new values, or =20
         press <B>Enter</B> if the existing values are      =20
         correct.                                    =20
                                                     =20
     =B0   Press <B>Enter</B> to save the new values or <B>Esc</B> to=20
         quit without changing.                      =20
                                                     =20
     The valid ranges:                               =20
                                                     =20
         For year:                                   =20
                                                     =20
             91-99 for the years 1991-1999           =20
             00-50 for the years 2000-2050.          =20
                                                     =20
         For month:  01-12.                          =20
                                                     =20
         For day:                                    =20
                                                     =20
             01-29 for February (29 is valid during  =20
             leap year only)                         =20
             01-30 for months with 30 days           =20
             01-31 for months with 31 days.          =20
                                                     =20
 <B>3.</B>  When the message code 023-02 is displayed,      =20
     change the current time.  To change the current =20
     time:                                           =20
                                                     =20
     =B0   Use the <B>left</B> and <B>right</B> <B>arrows</B> to move =
the   =20
         cursor.                                     =20
                                                     =20
     =B0   Use the numbers to enter the new values, or =20
         press <B>Enter</B> if the existing values are      =20
         correct.                                    =20
                                                     =20
     =B0   Press <B>Enter</B> to save the new values or <B>Esc</B> to=20
         quit without changing.                      =20
                                                     =20
     The valid ranges are:                           =20
                                                     =20
         For hour:  00-23                            =20
         For minutes:  00-59                         =20
         For seconds:  00-59.                         =
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>Run</B> <B>setup</B> =
<B>and</B>  =20
 <B>verify</B> <B>or</B> <B>set</B>  =20
 <B>Token-Ring</B>     =20
<A name=3DSPT4> <B>speed</B>           </A>
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                 </FONT></PRE></TD>
    <TD width=3D"75%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> When you run setup, the =
internal descriptions of the=20
 adapters installed in the 5494 are initialized.  If =20
 the 5494 has a Token-Ring adapter installed, setup  =20
 can be used to change the Token-Ring speed.         =20
                                                     =20
 Before running setup, see the configuration         =20
 worksheets or ask the customer to provide you with  =20
 the current Token-Ring speed.  (see <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRCONFG">"Displaying 5494</A>=20
 <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRCONFG">Configuration Information" in =
topic 6.2.2</A>).         =20
                                                     =20
 <B>1.</B>  Press <B>4</B> and <B>Enter</B> to access the setup =
function. =20
                                                     =20
 <B>2.</B>  Message code 024-01 will display, indicating    =20
     that the current data rate is displayed.        =20
                                                     =20
     If the data rate displayed is correct, press    =20
     <B>Enter</B>.  If not, press the <B>up</B> or <B>down</B> =
<B>arrow</B> and  =20
     <B>Enter</B> to change the rate.                       =20
                                                     =20
 <B>3.</B>  Press <B>Enter</B> to return to the CE main menu when  =20
     the message code 024-02 is displayed.            =
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>Run</B> <B>setup</B> =
<B>and</B>  =20
 <B>verify</B> <B>or</B>      =20
 <B>select</B> <B>Ethernet</B>=20
<A name=3DSPT4A> <B>media</B> <B>type</B>      </A>
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                 </FONT></PRE></TD>
    <TD width=3D"75%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> When you run setup, the =
internal descriptions of the=20
 adapters installed in the 5494 are initialized.  If =20
 the 5494 has an Ethernet adapter installed, setup   =20
 can be used to select or change the Ethernet media  =20
 type.                                               =20
                                                     =20
 Before running setup, see the configuration         =20
 worksheets or ask the customer to provide you with  =20
 the current Ethernet media type (see <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRCONFG">"Displaying</A>    =20
 <A =
href=3D"http://publibz.boulder.ibm.com/cgi-bin/bookmgr_OS390/BOOKS/co2v40=
02/6.2.2?DT=3D19961016091447#HDRCONFG">5494 Configuration Information" =
in topic 6.2.2</A>).    =20
                                                     =20
 <B>1.</B>  Press <B>4</B> and <B>Enter</B> to access the setup =
function. =20
                                                     =20
 <B>2.</B>  Message code 024-04 will display, indicating    =20
     that the current media type is displayed.       =20
                                                     =20
     If the media type displayed is correct, press   =20
     <B>Enter</B>.  If not, press the <B>up</B> or <B>down</B> =
<B>arrow</B> and  =20
     <B>Enter</B> to change the media type.                 =20
                                                     =20
 <B>3.</B>  Press <B>Enter</B> to return to the CE main menu when  =20
     the message code 024-02 is displayed.            =
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D"24%"><PRE><FONT size=3D2> <B>Test</B> <B>selected</B>   =

<A name=3DSPT5> <B>5494</B> <B>hardware</B>   </A>
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
                =20
